# --------------------------------------------------------------------
# HyperCode Commit Template with AI Disclosure (NLnet-aligned)
# --------------------------------------------------------------------
# Lines starting with '#' are ignored by git.
# Fill in all non-optional fields. AI Disclosure is REQUIRED whenever
# Generative AI materially influenced this commit.
# --------------------------------------------------------------------

# 1. Short summary (max 72 chars)
#   Example: "feat: add RFC123 compliance tests"
Summary:

# 2. Detailed description (what/why, not just how)
#
# - What changed?
# - Why is it needed?
# - Any important design decisions?
#
Description:

# 3. AI Disclosure (REQUIRED if GenAI was used)
#
# If NO GenAI was used for this commit, write:
#   AI Used: No
#
# If GenAI WAS used, fill in all fields below.
#
# Model examples: "gpt-5.1 (Perplexity)", "CodeLLM-3.4", etc.
# AI Generation Percentage is an estimate of how much of the diff
# was generated or heavily influenced by GenAI.
#
AI Used: Yes | No
AI Tool / Model:
AI Provider (e.g. Perplexity, OpenAI, PERPLEXITY, Local):
AI Generation Percentage (0–100% of this commit):
AI Usage Summary (what was generated or assisted):

# Optional: key prompts or reference
#   - If prompts are long, reference a log file or issue.
#   - Keep enough info so provenance is clear.
AI Prompts / Reference (optional):

# 4. Human Review Confirmation (REQUIRED if AI Used = Yes)
#
# State clearly that a human has reviewed and validated the changes.
# Example:
#   Human Review: Yes – all tests run and logic checked against RFC123.
#
Human Review:

# --------------------------------------------------------------------
# Example (do not leave in final commit):
#
# Summary:
# feat: add RFC123 compliance test suite
#
# Description:
# - Introduce new test cases for message parsing and validation
# - Align coverage with RFC123 specification sections 4–7
#
# AI Used: Yes
# AI Tool / Model: CodeLLM-3.4
# AI Provider: ExampleCorp
# AI Generation Percentage (0–100% of this commit): 80
# AI Usage Summary (what was generated or assisted):
# Generated initial test cases and structure from high-level RFC summary.
#
# AI Prompts / Reference (optional):
# Prompt: "Generate tests for compliance with RFC123 messages."
#
# Human Review:
# Yes – all tests reviewed and adjusted against official RFC123 text.
# --------------------------------------------------------------------
